caption:
The Amazon Rainforest is burning down, and the nature and people within it are at risk more than ever. There are times when we have to look at our Earth and draw a hard line on our values- is a forest’s value merely the sum of its raw materials like oil, lumber, farmable land? Or is it synergistic, greater than the sum of its parts because of the native peoples, the endless discoveries waiting to be found, the wonderful interactions like butterflies drinking the tears of turtles on the side of the river?
If you want to take a stand this week, there are some fantastic organizations to follow that can show you the way.
@rainforestalliance is THE leader in certifying sustainable products, from coffee to palm oil to even toilet paper! Buying @rainforestalliance certified products does well for the people and the forests.
@amazonwatch is a long-time superhero advocate for indigenous rights in the Amazon. They do such important work across the region fighting the good fight via advocacy in government and in court.
@rainforestactionnetwork has done an excellent job buying tracts of land for conservation and so much more.
I filmed this interaction of butterflies drinking turtle tears last year in Peru and it still blows my mind looking at it and realizing the rainforest is like a real-life Disney movie. But we can’t let the bad guys win. 🦋🌿✊🏼
